W: Me, too. It’ll be exciting. Honey, why are
you driving so slowly?
M: Don’t worry. We’ll be there in time because
the traffic isn’t heavy. Let’s have dinner
first.
W: Great. (pause) Oh, no! I can’t find our
tickets in my bag.
M: Check it one more time. I gave them to you
in the living room last night. Remember?
W: Oh! I think they are on my desk. I forgot to
put them in my bag.
M: What should we do?
W: Let’s take a U­turn over there. The traffic
sign is changing now. Can we make it on
time?
M: Yes, if I speed up.
